        "scenario": "Dead-letter queue fills up",
        "handling": "unhandled",
        "recommendation": "No consumer, no alert, no retention policy. If the DLQ backing store fills up, new DLQ writes may fail silently, causing total event loss. Deploy a DLQ consumer with alerting on queue depth > threshold and a replay mechanism."
