      "reason": "The retry strategy (3x exponential backoff), circuit breaker recovery, and at-least-once delivery guarantee all produce duplicate records. There is no deduplication at any layer. For an analytics service, this is not an edge case — it is a guaranteed data correctness failure that silently inflates every downstream metric. Must be fixed before production: add idempotency keys to writes or implement a deduplication layer in the consumer pipeline.",
      "routed_to": "MJ"
    },
    {
      "type": "integration_gap",
      "issue": "Dead-letter queue has no consumer, no alerting, and no replay path",
      "reason": "The DLQ currently functions as a black hole. Events routed there after 3 failed retries are never reprocessed, never alerted on, and will eventually be lost when retention expires or storage fills. This negates the value of having a DLQ entirely. Need a consumer service with replay capability and an alert on queue depth.",
      "routed_to": "MJ"
    }
  ],

  "confidence": {
